Your Honor,

I stand before this court today to plead guilty for the offense of driving whilst disqualified. I, David Lambert, a 55-year-old individual with no previous criminal record, acknowledge and accept the responsibility for my actions.

I deeply regret my decision to drive despite being aware of my disqualification. It was a thoughtless act that went against the court's previous order. I understand the gravity of my actions and I am truly embarrassed by my lack of judgment.

I want to assure the court that I am fully aware of the seriousness of this offense and the potential consequences it could have had. I understand that driving whilst disqualified undermines the safety and integrity of our roadways. I take full responsibility for my actions, and I deeply apologize for any harm that may have been caused as a result.

